>
  <p>Swollen legs, or lower limb oedema, can have several origins. In cardiology, right-sided heart failure is a common cause: when the heart struggles to circulate blood, it accumulates in the veins, allowing fluid to seep into the tissues.</p>

  <p>Other factors may also contribute, such as venous insufficiency, certain kidney diseases or medication side effects.</p>

  <p>A cardiology consultation helps understand the origin and propose appropriate management, combining attentive listening, clinical examination and targeted investigations.</p>
</DetailLayout>
